column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: This product exceeded my expectations! I have no complaints about this cologne. It smells fresh, vibrant, sporty, and very summery. This cologne is everything I wanted, and then some! I actually went from using Versace cologne to this masterpiece, and I will not go back! I bought this for $17, so naturally I was a little skeptical. But after trying it out for myself, I couldn't be any happier. This is a great every day cologne that can be worn casually or formally, it's that versatile! I will happily buy this again!

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: That's right, it smells kind of like a bowl of honeydew and cantaloupe at a Jamaican all-inclusive resort. Kind of sweet and fruity. Not very spicy. Not leathery or musky or dark or funky. It smells pretty decent. Some people will love it, and I doubt many will hate it. I think it smells fine. It's relatively powerful and long lasting. Unless you want to be smelled in a 10 foot radius and leave a cloud of scent in your wake, a single spray is fine and lasts all day.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: So originally i felt sketchy on ordering this as most may be, due to that you're not really sure how the item will turn out. But this has exceeded my expectations, it was placed in fantastic packaging and arrived flawlessly. However all other stuff aside, the actual cologne was incredible, the scent is hard to explain however its very sweet and refreshing. When applying it, it wasnt extremely strong like some however still is definitely an eye-drawing type of cologne, it has one of those smells which isnt artificial and cheap like axe but instead gives a lot of higher quality vibes. The scent lasts for quite a while ive noticed, with a few sprays youre good to go, and if youre trying to catch the attention of another, it will definitely increase your odds. Concluding with it all i would absolutely give this 5 stars, i definitely recommend it as its certainly worth the buy

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I'm extremely pleased with the cologne scent. If this review was based solely on the smell, it would have 5 stars. However, although the cologne arrived in its package and was still wrapped, the entire cap was smashed into four pieces. It didn't affect the cologne or the ease of use, but I find it important that you receive what you payed for without any damage. The cologne has a great smell, and it lasts about half a day. I would definitely recommend it, but know that the bottle may not be in one piece.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I bought all three, The Classic, The Voyage and the Blue. They all smell good. But in my personal preference, the King of all three is; Voyage.The Nautica Voyage. It smells very fancy like an cool ocean fresh but expensive elegant men perfume/cologne. All of the above in layers. For me using it in 30 degrees February winter It last a very long time 8-12+ and more if you use the right amount on you and some light spray on your clothes. You can also go light and it will last 3-6 hours depending on how much you use.Then in second place the Nautica Blue, it smells more sweet like hinting fruity sweet and fancy with tones of cool and sporty fancy smell and very very nice. It lasts on me the just the same time length as the other Voyage. And on third place the Classic, it smells nice but it’s too muskyand woody for my personal likes, as I like it more sweet than woody but it still smells really good. I can see some older mature men liking this one better.But the really interesting thing is that when I mix and use equal amounts of both Voyage and Blue together it creates a really incredible sweet fruity very fancy and expensive fragance that’s out of this world. It smells like cool oceanic sweet fruity sweet tones like peaches and cream with kind of pineapple hints, something really amazing to describe. I went to my daughters female doctor today and she and also her assistant who both entered at different times by themselves mentioned the really amazing smell in the room lol. Also my teenage daughter mentioned how great my perfume smelled the day before. And also another women in the elevator said “umm it smells really good in here” lol.So to me it’s a winner. Next time I will only buy the Nautica Voyage and the Nautica Blue, a perfect mix.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Was looking for a clean/refreshing fragrance. While I thought about purchasing 'Invictus Aqua', this was a very cheap alternative with great reviews. So I said "why not?".To my surprise, it has a VERY clean, refreshing scent to it. When you wear this, you bring a wonderful crisp smell into the dull, scentless room! And yes, people notice it too.Recieved a compliment from a female co-worker the first day I wore it, asked me what I was wearing. Like I said, it's a nice scent!Scent is A+. Projection lasts about 3-4 hours, afterwards being less strong but still noticable up close. Total longevity is about 6 hours since it's a light fragrance, not too shabby.Total recommend. If you don't like it, throw it in the corner. It's too affordable to not AT LEAST try first.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Over the years I had tried several different offices use toilette spray, and to my astonishment, most do not last the entire day.  Yesterday, working in the backyard in expanding the HE SHED in Southern California (Inland Empire), I came in for afternoon rest.  The better half (the wife), mentioned if I was wearing cologne.  She also said it smells nice and sweet.  I was stunned.  Why? Sweating and dusty from building materials, I did not expect to last that long.  Well...it not only met my wife's nose but continuing the entire day. The cologne is not only a grand bargain (bang for the buck) but appealing to those with a nose.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: First time purchasing a Nautica brand cologne. Had never smelled it before, but I had just ran out of my normal everyday cologne. I was looking for something a little different and came across Voyage. It had tons of gleaming reviews and $15 for a 3.4oz bottle was a steal. The smell is very fresh. Hints of fruit with a light musky after smell. I really liked it. The only reason I didn't give it 5 stars was because the longevity, in my experience is only about 3 hours. After than the cologne is hardly noticeable unless you literally have your face where you sprayed it earlier. But hey, for the price that's to be expected.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I've bought tons of stuff from Amazon, including cologne. This is only my second review I'm making because this is one incredible deal. Been using different colognes and this one seems to get a lot of good reaction. I am a waiter so of coarse I like to smell nice, and this cologne has had guests genuinely laughing while telling me I smell so good. My coworkers have all complimented it to an extreme. Cool Water has always been my favorite, but people seem to really like this.I can say it's legit, but it doesn't last forever. I guess it peeks shortly after you put it on and lasts for roughly 5-6 hours before the smell starts to vanquish.Overall, for the price... WOW. This cologne is a keeper in my collection as I don't like to wear the same everyday.Side note- the bottle and cap are my favorite out of all the colognes I use, very nice job there. Awesome stuff.

column4: I bought this for me and yes I am a woman. I used to buy Nautical Blue for my ex and I loved it so much I ended up wearing it. When I went back to buy Nautical Blue, it was out of stock so I settled for Voyage. I settled well. It is stronger than blue, very masculine, yet breezes and kool and fits me just fine. So even thought it's for men, I find that it works well with women too...afterall I buy it for myself and i love floral scent.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I didn't know what this smelled like before buying but I know Nautica to be a great brand. Only thing I was worried about was if it was going to be fake or something because that seems to be a problem with fragrances on Amazon. Well after using it for the first time today... I'd say it's the real deal. I literally just did one little spray on my chest before I left for work. I could smell it just fine pretty much through the whole day. I actually can still smell it and I have a very physical labor job (shipping industry) and I'd have to say that's pretty amazing. I'm glad I took the risk and would highly recommend this scent to anyone looking for an affordable cologne with a heavenly scent and long lasting!

column4: I purchased this cologne thru Amazon and this is the first time I've tried this particular cologne as I usually go for The Beat by Burberry and this smells great. You can go as subtle as you want with this if you chose or spray a little extra either way it's gonna stick all day long. Very good price for such a good long lasting smelling cologne.I have no idea why the 1 star reviews are complaining about receiving fake bottles unless purchased thru 3rd party on here even then for as cheap as this cologne is to buy wouldn't make sense to imitate it you normally see this happen on more expensive colognes.I have zero alcohol smell and my bottle came completely sealed in plastic and the bottle has the metal cap not the plastic I seen some people talking about.

Very good price for such a good long lasting smelling cologne.I have no idea why the 1 star reviews are complaining about receiving fake bottles unless purchased thru 3rd party on here even then for as cheap as this cologne is to buy wouldn't make sense to imitate it you normally see this happen on more expensive colognes.I have zero alcohol smell and my bottle came completely sealed in plastic and the bottle has the metal cap not the plastic I seen some people talking about.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I used to love this cologne a long time ago, but either the formula is different now or I received a counterfeit bottle. column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Not my bag, just too boring and typical.  The sort of scent that is like 1000 others in the same price range and makes the ladies walk on by to the guy wearing any scent from Cerutti or Versace.  I bought this in the search for a backup everyday scent.  Thallium Blue is my starter and still the best, lowest priced men's fragrance one can buy in my humble opinion, if it jives with your body chemistry.  I read reviews and had hopes that this might be the one to mix things up a little with the everyday scent, but nothing doing.  It might be great for some and gets some 5 stars, but I've bought men's fragrances online that had thousands of five-star reviews and smelled like an old ladies perfume. It's a gamble when you buy scent online with no way to check it out first. All you can do is give it a shot and don't spend too much money on anything you haven't checked out at a brick-and-mortar store and confirmed you like. This one you can check out at Walmart, which should say it all with regard to how typical and boring this scent is.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Great fragrance but you must spray a ton of it to really project the scent and make it last more than an hour. I’d suggest keeping a travel sized atomizer with u throughout the day toRefresh the scent.\Update: it is now my favorite summer scent! Where I thought it died out at the end of the day, I was wrong. My wife still smells it as I walk last. I bumped my review to 4 stars from 3 because it’s my favorite, and lasts a long time. But you still need to put a lot on. One spritz on all the vital spots like wrists, inner elbows, collarbone, neck, and sometime a few extra to really set it in stone. The smell is like fresh cut watermelon mixed with fresh cut grass. And those two scents are the best smells in the world to me. So if you love those, you will love this!

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I realize there is already thousands of positive reviews about this fragrance, and anybody looking to buy this has likely already bought it, but after using for over a year (daily; at work, at home, and everywhere else I went after a shower) I feel I must add my 5 cents.  To put it simply, Voyage might just be the best fresh/sporty/aquatic/clean out of shower fragrance available, period!  In a way Voyage is a "gateway fragrance", allowing people who normally don't wear cologne to try it out, love it, then go shopping for something better.  Perhaps this is the reason such a top-dollar smelling fragrance is priced so cheaply?Off the bat I am going to say that the biggest negative of Voyage is the longevity.  I am not going to sugar-coat or lie about this one, no matter how near-flawless the fragrance is and how much I absolutely love it, the longevity is lacking severely.  But if you are into fragrances you will notice that these fresh aquatics really just don't last long, it's a limitation of the ingredients used to make these smells.  Almost by definition the fresh/aquatics have next to no lasting power for some reason.  No idea why that is, as I can spray just a few sprays of a heavier EDT (or EDP) and get easily a whole day of longevity.  But of course the smell on those more powerful fragrances morphs into something completely different than what I smelled originally, usually not to my liking either.Until I blindly bought this fragrance, I was NOT a cologne wearing kind of guy, with only very special occasions being the exception.  I relied purely on my deodorant and shower soap to give me a fresh and clean smell. Never gave it much thought.  Then one day I decided I wanted a "signature scent", something people could smell years later and think "Hey, I remember that day and time in my life when I smelled something like that".  Not sure exactly what made me think of this originally, but I scoured Amazon for something I could try and see how it did for me.  My first pick was Nautica Voyage.  And boy, did I pick right!  (even well over a year ago, this was still extremely popular with many good reviews).I reluctantly sprayed on Voyage after my shower before work (never wore cologne to work to this point in my life), and was almost instantly reminded of the beach.  Thoughts of Kramer's "beach cologne" on Seinfeld came to mind, and I immediately thought "Oh...my...goodness, this smells so good!".  Fast forward to this day, and it is still my fragrance of choice, even after trying some EXTREMELY expensive and very well-liked/popular fragrances.Voyage just does something that the others I have tried (which is a LOT) don't event scratch.  It seems to do the impossible, not offend.  The smell is just so.. neutral and fresh.  It has this sweet, beach-like smell that is so incredibly wonderful!  And the smell doesn't morph into something completely different on dry-down, it just seems to have the same signature smell from first-spray to end-of-life.  Most other fragrances I have (cheap or expensive) change considerably from start to finish, but Voyage is truly a "what you smell is what you get" kind of fragrance.  Which is VERY rare from my experience.I only wish it lasted longer and had a stronger projection. I can spray on around 12 sprays and still not get through half my work day without needing to refresh (not quite as easy as it sounds, unfortunately).  With the insane popularity of this cologne I am hoping for a EDP to release that won't smell different but last longer and be more potent.  Might be a far fetch since this type of scent signature isn't known for it's lasting power or strength, but one can hope right? I get a whole day out of a EDT like Fahrenheit or Aqua Fahrenheit, which both have a very sweet smell to them, so why not the same lasting power from almost the exact kind of sweet smell from Voyage? (the "sweetness" smell from both of these fragrances is very close IMO).

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Loved the Scent, Longevity, and Cost. Ocean type scents usually don't last that long, but with this Cologne you can expect 7-9 hours, with about a 3 hour projection. For only around $15 dollars (I bought it for $12 on sale) this product is definitely a steal.You get an aquatic scent, with a hint of apple and lotus. Pretty masculine, something I'd wear to a high-prestige interview or something of that tier. I often get compliments on it when I wear it.Hint: A little goes a long way. I usually do 2 sprays on the neck and 1 spray for one wrist, and transfer it to the other one. You get a nice scent that lasts throughout the day without being offensive or too strong. It gives that great smell when you walk past somebody, or when they stand close. Really enhances your natural scent.A bottle would probably last you around a year, unless you're a cologne freak.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I've tried Nautica blue, island voyage, and voyage.This is certainly better than Nautica Blue. It's very similar to island voyage. However, it certainly lasts a long time. It is a mellow fresh scent. It feels a lot more "real" than blue did. It's not the manliest thing around but it is a worthwhile upgrade to Nautica blue. The big bottle choice is actually massive compared to the one you find at wally world and so it is certainly a good deal. If I had to guess the small choice is actually the large option at wally world. I like it. Out of the three, I think this may hit the sweet spot by a small margin over island voyage for scent. What is interesting was that Blue was my everyday scent, and I think I probably won't go back to it.The bottle itself looks very well made and looks classy.My only complaint is that a little goes a long way with this one so you have to be careful with the amount you use per spray if you want to use more than a spray or two as it is potent.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Came as promised, cheap, but good cologne. Honestly, there is fowl play about with the 'Voyage' series. I've gotten it from multiple vendors and have received 2 different kinds of bottles, slightly varied but the same name. One has a more quality feel, and thus a sweeter, more quality scent. The other (the one that I received) has a cheaper, plastic cap, and a more harsh, alcoholy scent to it. Again, both are boxed the same under the same line. I don't know if its just the bad batch that they sell off for cheap or what, but very annoying when its a guessing game as to what I'm getting. Both smell good, but there's an obvious inconsistency in final product. 2 stars for playing a guessing game when it comes to that, super frustrating, especially when you only know after you unbox it.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I was in desperate need (want) of an everyday Cologne in order to prevent my new-found love "Acqua Di Gio" by GA from losing its sex appeal. So, I did my research and stumbled upon Nautica Voyager right here on Amazon. I read most of the reviews and decided to go for it and I have no regrets to date. I used prime and I got it in 1.5 days after ordering. My girlfriend prefers its smell over the Acqua (she's wack I know) but I really think it's smell good also. Cologne is really subjective but I think for the price, it's worth it. It also stays on your clothes, though a bit mild, for about 18-24 hours making it a perfect choice for an everyday cologne.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I'm posting under my wife's account but this cologne was for me...I really like this.  No worries of getting a fake for me.  I used just a little on my shirt this morning before going out and 11 hours later I can still smell it in my shirt.  I would say this scent is a nice easy-breezy smell.  Just a little in the morning gives a nice fresh scent without being overwhelming.  It's like after a nice shower but better and lasts all day to a degree.  I would say this is a nice morning to afternoon scent.  It's light and not musky nor does it have a spice scent at all.  If going out to a formal dinner..or just out at night at all I wouldn't grab this stuff, I'd go with something more complex and heavier.  Love it, I recommend.  No reason to use a $50 cologne just to head out of the house for the day unless your are a CEO or something.  This is pleasant.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: First off, bought this directly from Amazon and it is the real thing. In my experience, if Amazon is the seller there is almost never an issue with perfumes.Given the price, this is an absolutely fantastic deal for a 3.4oz (100ml) bottle of fragrance. The best description I can give of the smell is that it is fresh. However, It is not like some of the summer fragrances which have citrus notes in them (e.g. CK one summer). The closest it is to the perfumes I have used would be Echo by Davidoff.Buying fragrances online is always a challenge so I'll list some other perfumes I use and like so that you may get an idea of my taste. Generally I like fragrances that are fresh and/or citrusy.Some I like - L'eau D'issey by Issey Miyake, Chrome by Azzaro, Acqua Di Gio by Giorgio Armani, Cool Water by Davidoff, CK One , CK One Summer, CK EternityDon't like - Dunhill Red, CK obsession

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: This Nautica Voyage cologne has an amazing scent. When you spray it, it lasts for a long time. Usually a spray or two on the neck or wrist will make it last much longer than on clothing because the heat from your arteries and the sweat on your skin complement and amplify the scent.Pros:The cologne lasts a very long timeThe cologne has an aquatic scent mixed with some citrus accents and musk.Cons:The only thing I would add is that buyers should be aware that cologne is made of chemicals and can change it's scent when exposed to warm temperatures and light. I bought this in the summer so when I got the cologne, it was quite warm to the touch. Some colognes smell downright nasty after being in the heat but as for this one, it still smelled good.

Also a little weak, could perhaps use more bass notes and a little bite to give it a more masculine, versatile, and fuller body in general. My main issue lies in the longevity, 5-7 sprays lasts me for a maximum of two hours. For the price, it's just OK. Nothing special.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: What a fantastic cologne, at an even more fantastic price. In fact the price on Amazon is so low that I consider this one of the greatest steals I've come across. This is the same cologne that received better marks than more expensive competitors on various websites, but you don't need a silly review with subjectively attributed points to know that this is a great product. The smell lingers for quite a long time, and the smell is breezy, slightly musky - light and oceanic, but still masculine. The first person to tell me how lovely I smelled was a friend's girlfriend. She said after I shook her hand (sprayed at the wrists) the smell lingered and she loved it.That was the second time I wore it going out, and dare I say the fragrance is very much a success.Now, in my opinion there are "better" colognes out there, but they will cost you upwards of $80-100 for a 3.4oz bottle. This product should be much more expensive, but it isn't. Gentlemen, do yourselves a favor and get it now.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Definitely worth it. I'm not a huge cologne guy. I don't really want people to be smelling me all day regardless of how good it is. But this cologne is good because it wasn't expensive at all and I've had it for over a year and I'm not even halfway done. In fact I really use this almost every day. I do notice though that it doesn't last long and gets a mild alcohol smell if you spray to much but goes away quickly if you spray too little. I've started spraying it on my clothes more than myself because I find it brings out the sweet ocean smell more than the heavy cologne smell. Idk if that's just because I'm using the product wrong or it works better on fabrics. Whatever that's my 2 cents.I do recommend this product through.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Everyone is different and if you've tried many different colognes by now, you should already know this. So when many reviewers mention that this cologne lasts throughout the day, I just had to try it. Me personally, I would much rather use a cologne that smelled just "okay" but lasts long rather than vice-versa. Therefore, I didn't really care how this would smell.The smell from what I can best describe it as is having a strong and sweet kiwi fruit smell. If fruity colognes are not your thing, you might be put off by this one. This actually smells very close to Paris Hilton for Men but I'm sure for a fraction of the price.The disappointment came in that this cologne does not last very long on my skin. I use about 3-4 sprays in the morning but by midday, it's pretty much gone. I can get like a quick sniff of it but it does not hold up to my standards of a cologne. For the price I paid for this though, I can hardly get mad. But again, everyone is different so your experience may differ from mine. You'll just have to try it.FYI: To date, my perfect cologne remains to be Jean Paul Gaultier both in smell and longevity.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I don't understand the "fake" product reviews. These are the real deal. I even checked the manufactured fresh date on the website "checkfresh" I bought this in October/November 2016 and by entering the serial code found on the sticker at the bottom of my bottle (1 Letter, 11 numbers), I found out my batch was made in August of 2016. This tells me 2 things... THAT THE BOTTLE IS PRETTY FRESH, BUT MORE IMPORTANTLY, since IT SHOWED UP ON THE INDEPENDENT WEBSITE, THIS BOTTLE IS AUTHENTIC as the batch codes are unique. One spritz of this bottle lasts a whole day for me. It smells like a refreshing scent of stepping out of the shower with light body wash scent. IT SMELLS GOOD! A+ I did not have the opportunity to try this in the store and I went on a whim of reading all these stellar reviews so I was pleasantly surprised when I experienced the fragrance. Especially since Amazon doesn't allow refunds for perfumes/cologne as it contains flammable alcohol.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: In my short 27 years I have only used two scents on an ongoing basis (let's not discuss the AXE body spray craze we all went through in high school). These were Curve for Men by Liz Claiborne and Acqua di Gio by Giorgio Armani.Curve I wore as I was going through puberty and matured throughout high school. I used it for a few years in college as well as I always seemed to get compliments on it. As my tastes grew I then got hooked on di Gio and used it up until now. I was getting a bit tired of it and actually stopped using cologne for about a year or two. I figured I would experiment and try something new as I did miss those two sprays in the morning after a shower which had me smelling great all day.I picked up Voyage by Nautica as it was at a very decent price and it seemed to have favorable reviews. They were for the most part spot on. This is a very fresh, clean scent, nearly akin to a fresh set of laundry after retrieving it from the dryer. I asked my girlfriend who for 6 years has known me to wear di Gio, and she loves it. She likes the fresh scent and says its literally a breath of fresh air.If you're looking to experiment, try this cologne out. I'm not a connoisseur by any means but I think its a fresh scent that anyone could go with. And at this price point you're not really losing out. As previous reviews have stated make sure you have the authenticity sticker at the bottom of the bottle. The risk of getting a lemon is there but it seems like the majority of the bottles are authentic!

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: The Short and Simple- Amazing, crisp smell- Not too strong but not too faint eitherI was looking for a new cologne and went through Amazon's top cologne and this was the #1 seller so I figured it had to be good. Read all of the reviews and it sounded like this was my kind of smell. This is definitely not your manly scent (think like dark, vanilla aromas) but more like your crisp, fresh, citrus smell. Not so citrus-y that it smells like a perfume but almost exactly what you'd expect from Nautica. The scent actually fits their image so well. I've been using it since day 1 and love it.Be sure not to over-do the spray. I do one spray on my left wrist, then I dab my right wrist and then using both wrists, dab both sides of my neck. It's just the right amount of cologne without being too overpowering. You don't want someone to be able to smell it on you from a mile away. Not even from a foot away. You want them to be able to smell it when they get close to you.

However, I have worn this once or twice on a lazy weekend and to the gym. You cannot go wrong at all with buying this fragrance given it’s incredible price.The only reason I took a point off was simply because it’s a rather “linear” scent that does not really evolve or change in the dry down. But that’s to be expected from a lot of fresh aquatics.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I would most strongly recommend this product for high school/college individuals who are beginning to understand the importance of good fragrances but are restricted in terms of money.  I was there once too!  However, this fragrance does not smell cheap in any regard and holds an integrity that is very clean and sharp. What I love so much about this fragrance is its longevity.  On clean, remotely moist skin it will last 8-12 hours.  It is also fairly potent for an aquatic fragrance, so easy on the trigger, two-three sprays on chest/neck will do it.  It opens its top-notes with a fruity presence that smells likes apples and settles quickly into a fresh/clean/floral green accord and settles its base in a very pleasant and masculine woody/aquatic contrast.  I find, like most aquatic fragrances it is best appreciated during the late spring/summer seasons.  For the price and quality this fragrance is hard to beat.  I was an avid wearer in my high school years and have been through many fragrances.  I still have profound respect and continue to come back with reliance to this one. Pick it up now, and remember to purchase through Amazon LLC. instead of a third party selling on Amazon to ensure authenticity.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I am in college and found this cologne to be one of the best value colognes. I received this in a well packaged box with no issues. I don't put on cologne every day, more like once or twice a week with two to three spritz each time. With that rate, it seems like this would definitely last me more than a year, maybe two. The smell is a slightly sweet smell, very pleasant. I get some compliments using this, and this is not overbearing at all. The scent lasts for most of the day, and sometimes I smell it in the old clothes I wore from previous use.  I'd recommend this for a spring type of feel. It doesn't seem to have much musk. I have several colognes, but I am no expert on scents so take this review with a grain of salt. This is still my favorite budget cologne.
column10: I am in college and found this cologne to be one of the best value colognes. I received this in a well packaged box with no issues. column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Purchased this for my husband and it has a fruity sort of scent. It's definitely for men and smells good and lasts a decent amount of time. It might not go all day, but it really depends on the man. I purchased this "nose-blind" and am very happy with the purchase. I recommend however going to a store such as Macy's and then testing the product, then purchasing through amazon as the price here is WAY better than that at Nautica.com and other retailers.PS: There seemed to have been an issue with some fake products, but believe that this one is real. However, the box that I received has a slightly different design than that of the picture, so they may have changed the box/product/formula, the picture shows a fake one (unlikely as it's the same pic on nautica.com), or I actually do have a fake one that still smells lovely.
column10: Purchased this for my husband and it has a fruity sort of scent. It's definitely for men and smells good and lasts a decent amount of time. It might not go all day, but it really depends on the man. I purchased this "nose-blind" and am very happy with the purchase. I recommend however going to a store such as Macy's and then testing the product, then purchasing through amazon as the price here is WAY better than that at Nautica.com and other retailers.PS: There seemed to have been an issue with some fake products, but believe that this one is real. However, the box that I received has a slightly different design than that of the picture, so they may have changed the box/product/formula, the picture shows a fake one (unlikely as it's the same pic on nautica.com), or I actually do have a fake one that still smells lovely.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Always being self conscious about how I'm smelling around people, I decided to look for a cheap and reliable solution where I could see reviews of a product, rather than take a guess in a retail store.....That being said, I'm glad I made the decision because the average votes for this cologne don't lie.Within the first week after switching to this cologne, people started commenting on how good I smell. I had never received as many compliments from any other cologne that I had purchased and even though that seems small....That was definitely a deal breaker.  This cologne has a very unique smell. The only smell I can relate this to, is like walking into a Macy's store where all the bad perfumes are gone. If you're looking for that special person to notice you a little more, or if you generally want a huge confidence booster, THIS IS THE WAY TO GO.The only cons to this product is that it is a "little" watered down. You will probably end up having to spray twice as much as you usually do with other colognes which isn't too much of a set back. It does not smell cheap; it smells very fresh, and if you use it like me and put it on every time you leave your dorm or apartment, then this will last you about 2 months. I'm going to be buying two after writing this review since I just finished my old bottle.Only reason not to recommend this to someone, is so that you can keep this secret to yourself.  Would give a 4.5/5 if I could, but you know..Amazon thinks that integers are prettier.Hope this helped,Cheers!~Broccan

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Everyone on the popular forums of the internet seem to rave about this cologne its amazing fragrance. I gave it a whirl since it was on sale for $13 thinking I was getting a great deal. I open the box and take the lid off the bottle and spray the blue mist into the air. Immediately I lunge back from getting a whiff of it as it reminds me of the scent of a "stink bug". The cologne smells of dead bugs with a fruity note. The cologne itslef reminded me more of women's perfume than a man's. I do not know what everyone is raving about, but I would never put this on my body as it gave me a headache as soon as I sprayed it. I will be sticking with Versace's "Pour Homme" for now even though it is quite expensive. I am still on the look out for a cheaper cologne that smells manly. (I don't know anything about colognes so keep that in mind.)

column4: Smells like sweet pickle juice and ripened hachiya persimmon.  It smells sweet, with a snap of pickling spice(dill, etc. not necessarily sour though). This scent is just not for me, I was disappointed by it.  In addition to not liking the scent, like others have mentioned, the scent does not last long at all, I'll mist the heck out of my jacket and shirt collar, only to have it wear off in 2 - 3 hours.The one that I got said "Coty" on it, plus when I opened the package it smelled very moldy, I even washed the bottle with soap to get rid of it(probably had moisture in the box before it was wrapped at the factory).  Overall, disappointed, not sure what to do with it.

column4: I wholeheartedly believe that I would have trouble attracting women if not for Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray 3.4 oz.  Before I started wearing this “scent”, I would approach women and they would say “get out of here, guy!” I’m an average-sized man (six feet on a tall day, 5’10’’ on a short one) and make sure to watch all the stand-up comedy I can, so that women will find me funny.  Alas, these two factors were not enough.  Enter-- Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray 3.4 oz. WOW has this “scent” made a difference! Now, ladies are always saying things like “your jokes are good” and “is it just me, or are you six feet tall?” (Even on my short days!!!)Let’s move on to the scent itself.  Have you ever opened a ripe papaya on the shoreline of some tropical and exotic island?  I haven’t, but I imagine it would be something like Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray 3.4 oz.  To me, this “scent” reminds me of my family vacation to South Carolina, only sexier.  That trip was super fun!  But I digress…Basically, I recommend this “scent” to anyone and everyone, especially if you are having a hard time with the ladies.  It even fits in my pocket in case I need an emergency spritz.  Five stars all the way, Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray 3.4 oz!!!**the photo attached is back in my pre-Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I buy Nautica Voyage every time it runs out because of its good and calming sweet citrus smell - it is a bit light, but that is not to say that it is weak. It is not a fragrance that reaches out and touches the world, but I don't want to be known as the obnoxious over-worn fragrance master irritator of all times anyways; somehow, you almost cannot put too much on. It is more of an up close and personal fragrance, and, I would say, a bit of a unisex fragrance. I am a man, but I would even wear a perfume if I loved the smell enough lol. This fragrance dies slowly over an 8 hour period if you are concerned about that sort of thing. Nautica Voyage would make an excellent refresher to have with you wherever you are going. Enjoy this one!
column10: I buy Nautica Voyage every time it runs out because of its good and calming sweet citrus smell - it is a bit light, but that is not to say that it is weak. It is not a fragrance that reaches out and touches the world, but I don't want to be known as the obnoxious over-worn fragrance master irritator of all times anyways; somehow, you almost cannot put too much on. It is more of an up close and personal fragrance, and, I would say, a bit of a unisex fragrance. I am a man, but I would even wear a perfume if I loved the smell enough lol. This fragrance dies slowly over an 8 hour period if you are concerned about that sort of thing. Nautica Voyage would make an excellent refresher to have with you wherever you are going. Enjoy this one!

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Perhaps I got one of the fabled fakes or bad bottles? The one I got seems completely legit to me, and the scent is very disappointing, though maybe not objectively "bad".I bought this in 2016 because I was looking for a starting point into cologne, and this is clearly one of the most highly rated on Amazon. I was looking for something light, not alcohol-y, and very aquatic / clean smelling. Unfortunately, the bottle that I got is actually very strong (in a bad way, for me), does smell quite heavily of alcohol, and while I can definitely get a hint of the aquatic aspect that the cologne purportedly has, it's hugely overshadowed by the heavy musk of whatever else is in there.Initially, I thought this was just a shock because I'm not used to wearing cologne. I would first wear a little bit around the house to see how it set into my skin over time, thinking it would eventually get good (perhaps just the top note was bad?). Eventually I started to wear a very trace amounts to work to try to adjust to it, eventually going down to one single spray on one wrist. Even this was too heavy and musky, and funnily enough, did last all day, and ended up giving me a slight headache. I felt embarrassed to have it on, in fear that other people may be smelling what I was smelling. After this, I stopped using it altogether.As a funny anecdote, I had a rather unpleasant repeat customer at my workplace that would come in wearing this stuff every single time - I could tell it was this scent without an ounce of doubt. Eventually my coworkers would start comment on his "terrible" cologne after he came in, and I could actually tell if he had been in because of the heavy scent cloud that would persist when he came by. I'll chalk most of this up to the guy probably using WAY too much cologne in general, but experiencing this scent on someone else definitely solidified my thoughts about it not being something I ever want to wear again.Overall, I gave it 2 stars instead of 1, because maybe I just have the exact chemistry required to dislike this cologne, and it's definitely not the worst thing I've ever smelled. It's also a very fair price, and does seem to last a while (even though I think I dislike the base notes the most). However, this is something I'd recommend you go into a store to try first, as if I had done so myself, I definitely would not have bought an entire bottle of this. Additionally, by doing this, you may come across a bottle of what, in my head, this scent was actually "supposed" to smell like and decide accordingly (apparently there was a reformulation, and perhaps a lot of fakes. Hard to tell with scents though).

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I honestly purchased this due to the great price a few weeks ago, and had never smelled it previously. I read the reviews and just couldn't pass up the deal.I'm extremely happy that I didn't pass on it. This has become one of my favorite colognes, and it is now in heavy rotation along with Armani Code.This is a 'water' cologne, and some people just don't like that style...and that's just fine. I love the style, and think this is one of the best smelling colognes in it.It's also quite long lasting. I generally apply it before work, and it's still noticeable when I'm getting home ~10 hours later(at very close distance)All in all, a great scent that I'm really glad I jumped on. I jumped at an even cheaper price on Nautica Blue, and while I'm not as enamored with the scent, it's not too bad.
column10: I honestly purchased this due to the great price a few weeks ago, and had never smelled it previously. I read the reviews and just couldn't pass up the deal.I'm extremely happy that I didn't pass on it. This has become one of my favorite colognes, and it is now in heavy rotation along with Armani Code.This is a 'water' cologne, and some people just don't like that style...and that's just fine. I love the style, and think this is one of the best smelling colognes in it.It's also quite long lasting. I generally apply it before work, and it's still noticeable when I'm getting home ~10 hours later(at very close distance)All in all, a great scent that I'm really glad I jumped on. I jumped at an even cheaper price on Nautica Blue, and while I'm not as enamored with the scent, it's not too bad.

column4: It smells good but very subtle. You have to put you nose very near to feel the scent. Also the bottle are really strange, usually inside the box there's thick paper to protect the bottle. For this one, there isn't. Besides, the code number was printed on the nylon cover which supposed to be on the box and the bottle.  I have tested it. It does not last long. About 1h30m to 2 hours. Then I went to Kohl's and tried the tester bottle there. The result is the tester bottle lasts for 6 hours. Hell. Did any one buy this perfume with Amazon? Do you have the same problem? It was sold by Amazon, not a third party.

column4: This is my second bottle of Nautica Voyage. The first one was a 1.7oz bottle from Kohls for $34.99. So when I searched Amazon and found this deal for double that amount (3.4 oz) for $18.30 after tax. I read some of the reviews that they had received an imposter cologne because the cap was plastic.Well let me tell you those reviews are bogus. The cap design likely had changed since they last purchased because the look of the cap, scent, and strength. It was exactly what was expected... Nautica Voyage! Don't believe those reviews and take advantage of this unbeatable deal!

column4: At first I was pretty happy with this purchase. It smelled nice and while I noticed the scent only lasted an hour or two, I got a 3.4 ounce bottle when I only paid for a 1.7 ounce bottle and I paid like 1/3 normal retail price.The other day while shopping at a department store, I saw this cologne at the fragrance counter. I gave it a quick spray on my wrist (free cologne!) and noticed it was much stronger and more pleasant than mine. The single spray also lasted longer than the 2-3 I usually use.I'm seriously starting to believe I received a knock-off. The price is almost too good and the scent isn't as good as the stuff from the department store. Amazon should look into this.

column4: Got this originally for me, but ended up giving it to my dad as a christmas gift. column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Reviews are what brought me to buy this. Well I can say they were right and I'm glad I bought it. This smells amazing with just one simple spray. Everytime I meet someone they tell me I smell nice. My lady friend always likes it and has sprayed her self lol. For the money it's more than worth it. Would recommend, and I have; after the fact of my two friends asking where I got and the price. Not only that it really helps my dragon I ride to school everyday feel better about being under me. He enjoys the brisk smell on the way thru the air as we cut off the fellow dragons. Sometimes he actually claims to get more miles per gallon because his stress levels go down from the smell and help him cruise through the air better. Practically this cologne is likely to help you with your vehicles mileage of you own a dragon or giant bald eagle(depending on country). 10/10 would buy for my master again.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I'm not one too experienced with colognes, so I'm not sure how long it's supposed to last once applied. I can get perhaps 4-6 hours - but the strength definitely tapers off as the day goes on.  At the end of the day - not much there at all.Unlike some others who have commented, I don't think this is fake, but I do think that once it changed ownership, something about it may have changed.  Overall it's a good everyday product that is a good value.Buying this type of thing over the internet is a bit risky but I was swayed by the price and the fact that it was sold by Amazon.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: A "best bang for your buck" fragrance, Nautica Voyage is easily worth the 20 dollars or so that you'd spend to buy a large bottle. The apple, lotus, and mimosa notes blend very nicely to create a perfect casual summer cologne. Voyage goes on a little scratchy at first, but after 15 minutes or so it settles in and creates a beautiful scent trail. It's citrusy, with just enough sweetness to take the edge off, and the right kind of florals to round it out. What I like most about Voyage is that there's this root-beer like fizz in the mix of it all as well. What you ultimately get is an appealing and addictive accord that persists for several hours before settling into a skin scent around the 3 to 5 hour mark. Projection is average. Voyage is appropriate for any age and best suited for Spring and Summer.
column10: A "best bang for your buck" fragrance, Nautica Voyage is easily worth the 20 dollars or so that you'd spend to buy a large bottle. The apple, lotus, and mimosa notes blend very nicely to create a perfect casual summer cologne. Voyage goes on a little scratchy at first, but after 15 minutes or so it settles in and creates a beautiful scent trail. It's citrusy, with just enough sweetness to take the edge off, and the right kind of florals to round it out. What I like most about Voyage is that there's this root-beer like fizz in the mix of it all as well. What you ultimately get is an appealing and addictive accord that persists for several hours before settling into a skin scent around the 3 to 5 hour mark. Projection is average. column4: I purchased this cologne as a Christmas gift for my boyfriend. I was very hesitant about how good it would be because of the price and it’s usually a better idea to smell a perfume or cologne prior to buying it but I was thoroughly impressed with the scent. I wanted to buy my boyfriend a real cologne because he has used old spice spray cologne foe the longest time and he’s 22 so I wanted to get a real cologne. This is a very light scent, not woodsy or spicy at all. I’m not sure how to describe the scent of men’s cologne but I’m trying. It’s a perfect scent for someone transitioning into wearing cologne and a perfect day time scent for sure. The packaging of the cologne is so nice as well. He loves and and I sure do!

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: It has a really fresh smell, almost aquatic but not exactly... It's kind of hard to describe. Check out Fragrantica for what each of the notes contains. Anyway, my girlfriend loves it, and so do I. The only issue I have with it is that it does not last as long as I would like (probably because it's an Eau de Toilette as opposed to Eau de Parfum or Parfum). Also, the sillage is not very high. All this means is that it does not radiate very far from your body which can be good or bad. Overall, it's a great cologne especially if you just want to try it out!
column10: It has a really fresh smell, almost aquatic but not exactly... It's kind of hard to describe. Check out Fragrantica for what each of the notes contains. Anyway, my girlfriend loves it, and so do I. The only issue I have with it is that it does not last as long as I would like (probably because it's an Eau de Toilette as opposed to Eau de Parfum or Parfum). Also, the sillage is not very high. All this means is that it does not radiate very far from your body which can be good or bad. Overall, it's a great cologne especially if you just want to try it out!

column4: This is a cheap knock-off of Nautica which I have been using for years now. Such low price tag in itself should have been a red flag for me. But, I went with the star rating of other reviewers, hoping that I had stumbled upon a great find on Amazon. Bad idea!The perfume lasts less than 20 minutes on you and I'm not even exaggerating. You can as well spray some water on yourself instead of this perfume and you would feel no different. Stay away from this unless you want to burn your money needlessly.

column4: This item seems diluted and does not meet the standard of Nautica Voyage by Nautica for Men.  I previously purchased Nautica Voyage (in the past 2 years from a department store) and still have some of the product.  I compared the recent purchase of NV that I received from my AMAZON purchase with the same product purchased from a department store and found the AMAZON NV to have a faint fragrance and essentially not be the same product that I had purchased from the department store (Although the name is identical).  I am disappointed and this makes me suspicious of online products and hesitant to make similar future purchases online.  Maybe it makes me suspicious of the quality of Nautica Voyage?  Either way - something is not consistent.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: With most aquatic fragrances, they don't last long. Voyage, however, is an aquatic that lasts VERY long. Projection is well above average, also. Being a low-class designer too! This exceeded all expectaions. The perfumer is very good, one of the best too, if you care.Now, the notes and actual smell of the fragrance is stunning. This fragrance is pretty linear, but it doesn't matter if its great throughout the whole period. Starting with a very fruity vibe, with some lavenderish-cleanish-fresh smell. It blends down with some soapy notes, with the fruit staying in there strong; I can also get a little musk in there. Overall, its a very sweet scent, and very masculine for a sweet scent too. Great for the younger crowd, but also exceptional for the 30+'s too. Perfect for highschool, college.Its mostly versitle; mostly intended for the spring and summer. But with the amazing longevity, it can even last in the winter. Perfect for signature scents, I would say. And with the price, you really can't get any better.I don't get the Cool Water similarity. They're very different. Cool water isn't sweet. Its fresh and lavenderish. Despite all the marketing, cool water is actually more 'green' than aquatic to me. Voyage is a true aquatic, that lasts amazingly long. Get this instead of Cool Water. You won't regret it.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I'm a 22 year old college student who hasn't really started to wear cologne. Well I'm about to graduate from school and I've got myself a big boy internship. I wear dress shoes and ties and I think it's about time for me to also grow out of my teenage body sprays (axe/old spice). I had very mixed feelings about cologne in general. It always felt like something only older men wear, like something that was too expensive. I've also had some bad run-ins with people who spray way too much fragrance and could clear a room.I decided to check to see what kind of products amazon had. Nautica Voyage was and still is sitting at the Number #1 best seller in Men's Cologne, so I though I'd give it a try. I was not disappointed. Overall, I'm ecstatic about this fragrance. I'm not a scent connoisseur or anything but it smells great. I would almost describe it as taking a shower after laying out on the beach. It's light and airy, but also distinctly masculine. It's not overpowering in any way and I've worn it to work, school, and social functions without any objection. Be sure to only do a few sprays though. (I two sprays on the front of my wrists and rub it into my neck/chest).My girlfriend loves it. Every time she hugs me now, she takes an extra second to smell my chest. I've also received a few compliments from friends (if they get close enough to smell it).I was a bit concerned because of all of the reviews about fake products. I went with the default seller and everything seems fine. My bottle does have a plastic cap, but has a serial number on the bottom sticker. The smell also seems legit and lasts for quite awhile. The concern about the cap might just be an updated bottle design.-Overall, I'm glad I bought it. For the cheap price, I consider it a great starter cologne. It's a fragrance that seems to work in almost every situation and I have yet to meet a person who hasn't liked it. If you find this review helpful, please hit the "Yes" button below. Also feel free to let me know if you have any questions and I'll be happy to answer them!

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: Longevity is something you search for in a designer fragrance, and Nautica Voyage delivers. One to three sprays of this scent, and you'll be able to smell it the next day. Seriously. I have smelled and tested hundreds of colognes, and Voyage is near the top for a lasting fragrance. This lasts longer than Chrome or even Obsession. 1 Million might last a bit longer.You get this fantastic long lasting scent from the minuscule amount that the sprayer puts out. After all, that's why we buy expensive cologne, right? See for yourself. Go to a store. Spray a fragrance card. Smell that card in a day or two, and it will still smell like Voyage.Spectacular aquatic scent. Fresh and clean. Somewhat akin to Cool Water, but better, and oh so long lasting. Nautica makes many appealing aquatic fragrances. This is my favorite. Find it in retail stores for $30+ an ounce, then come to Amazon for a better price on a wonderful product.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I bought this cologne because it was recommended by many and the very low price. I read some reviews and seemed like every so often someone got a bad bottle, a fake maybe. I decided to take the chance and hope I get a good one. I received a leaking bottle with the metal peeling from the cap, not a deal breaker as long as it smelled as good as it usually does. A few sprays and it smelled awful, like window cleaner/alcohol and a dash of cologne, it really hurts the nose. The only good thing (for this cologne) is that it does not last long, I put it on before work and asked a co-worker if she could smell it (maybe 2 hours after i put it on) and she could not unless her nose was an inch from my shirt. It was around 13 dollars so I'm glad I didn't waste more money, but this is something you find at a flea market.Take a $15 gamble or spend a little more at a store for a legit one.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I bought this cologne on clearance at Marshalls for around $10 and at first hated it. I was not expecting to get a fruity cologne. It was definitely a blind buy and I regretted buying it for the longest time. This was before I learned about the dry-down period of colognes. After a while, they interact with your skin and can change completely in terms of smell. This is one of the colognes that I've tried that does this. At first, you are bombarded by the scent of melons. I mean extremely sweet melons...and a lot of them. After it dries down, it is still very sweet and fruity but the melon dies down a bit and blends with some of the other notes to produce the perfect summer day fragrance. I could wear this walking on the beach in the middle of June and reapply it before going to a barbecue that night. It is very versatile within the warmer seasons. Absolute recommendation from me if you enjoy sweeter fragrances.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: At first I was a bit skeptical about the purchase, what with all the people saying they got a fake version or something like that, so I wasn't sure what I would receive. Upon receiving it I was sure it was real since it was in a sealed box and the bottle had the proper stickers on it with a good labeled cap.Really glad I decided to try this out because I love it. It has a very "fresh", fruity wood smell to it. It's not too overpowering either, has a nice subtle way about it. You can always apply more if you want a stronger aroma but a couple of sprays after a shower will last a good amount of time, I'd say like 4-6 hours, maybe more depending on how much you use.All in all a great purchase, especially at this price. Definitely recommend.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: This has got to be the most perfect scent for summer!  Its a very nice fruity, soapy floral scent and since there is no citrus in it like typical aquatics, it is not harsh at all and very very pleasant to the nose.  And when I say floral, it does that mean that it smells feminine at all, it just has that just hoped out of the shower fresh feeling.  The best way for to describe it is think of like a nice fresh body wash and makes you feel fresh and clean, this is pretty much that smell.This cologne gets raved on by basenotes and fragantica as being one of the "best cheapie" fragrances you can get.  Longevity and sillage are also pretty impressive as well for an aquatic (6-7 hours on my skin).  Definitely a fragrance for a younger guy in high school or college.

column4: I have always been an avid cologne consumer. my signature scent as of the past year has been BVLGARI man Extreme. And while that still is my favorite cologne, my bottle ran dry about a week ago. I had a first date planned with this girl, and i kind of forgot until she reminded me, and i thought "oh crap i dont have cologne". i was right near my local retail store, and i ran in. No BVLGARi. so i asked for some help from the girl working and she recommended this fragrance. when i first tried it on i wasnt too impressed, but impressed enough to get the 1.7oz bottle since i just needed SOMETHING. i put it on after my grooming regimen and ran out the door. by the time i got to the girls apartment to pick her up, the scent had seemingly settled into a much more clean/fresh aquatic scent that i really enjoyed. by the end of the night i had received a very nice compliment about my smell. so i highly recommend it for a nice summer day/night fragrance. and for the price, you just cant beat it.

column2: Nautica Voyage By Nautica For Men. Eau De Toilette Spray, 100 ml
column4: I went looking for a new cologne.  I like a simple, masculine, old-fashioned fragrance.  I was drawn to Nautica Voyage, but the salesperson said it was cheap and wouldn't last.  I ended up buying two other colognes, both excellent:  Skulls and Roses and Armani Code.  But, then I still bought the bottle of the Voyage anyway (great price).  To my surprise, Voyage has lasting power no less excellent than the more expensive ones, and I love it.  It's become my regular and the other more expensive ones are "for a change."  For me, there is something almost addictive about Nautica Voyage.
